    - The person who wants to share the project must include the actual authors of the software.
    - The person who wants to share the project must not present himself or herself as THE author of the project.
    - The person who wants to share the project must not include all or part of the source code.
(2) Modification of the project is authorised under the following conditions:
    - The project may only be freely modified during personal use.
    - A person who wants to create a game modification and make it available to the public must apply the CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license or the CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license to it.
    - A person who wants to create a game modification and make it available to the public must also include the actual authors of the original software.
(3) The use of the project or its modifications for commercial purposes is prohibited.
(4) The distribution of developer accounts and keys is prohibited.
(5) The distribution of the source code is prohibited.
(6) In case where the user discovers a serious bug in the software that is capable of harming other users' data and their hardware, he/she has an immediate obligation to inform the project authors.
(7) BYRg Studio and the project volunteers are not liable for damages caused by misuse of the software or running unstable versions of the software.
(8) In case of a change or update of the licence, previous versions of the software remain under the old licence, unless the authors wish a permanent change, whereby they must explicitly inform users of the changes at least 14 days before they are implemented.
(9) By downloading or sharing or running the software, the user voluntarily accepts all of the above conditions.
